-------------------------------------------------------------------------
|									|
|   Assigment name    : permutations					|
|   Expected files    : *.c *.h						|
|   Allowed functions : puts, malloc, calloc, realloc, free, write	|
|									|
-------------------------------------------------------------------------

Write a program that prints all the permutations of a string given as an argument.

The solution must be provided in alphabetical order.

We will not test your program with strings containing duplicates (e.g., 'abccd').

For example, this should work:
$>./permutations a | cat -e
$>a$
$>./permutations ab | cat -e
$>ab$
$>ba$
$>./permutations abc | cat -e
$>abc$
$>acb$
$>bac$
$>bca$
$>cab$
$>cba$
